Buona Beef is a classic Chicago restaurant. It’s designed to be fast for those on the go or a relaxing neighborhood restaurant. The food is absolutely great. I enjoy the Anthony Rizzo which is a beef with a little red sauce. Buona even commits part of the proceeds to Rizzo’s charity. I have been a fan of B-B when they opened a restaurant in Berwyn almost 40 years ago. They are consistently good, restaurant is clean and you can’t find better French fries. The minestrone soup is one of my favs in the cold winter when I’m walking. After all, buona means “good” in Italian.

First let me start this review by saying I love pizza I could literally eat it everyday thin crust deep dish in between. That being said if the opportunity arises for me to try something in my city that has yet to hit my taste buds I'm always happy to oblige. In this particular instance I was familiar with the pizza from this establishment. They first started having pizzas when they had a fine dining full service Italian restaurant downtown that's when I first tried it it was delicious. Then I had the pleasure of having the same Pizza a few times in the suburbs when I would happen upon one of their locations even through the drive-through my pizza came out perfectly cooked just enough flavor and the sauce the sausage the cheese in the crust together to make it a delicious pie.  Tonight's pizza was not anything like that it was Bland. It tasted like it needed more sauce or like the sauce needed more something. I couldn't pinpoint it. But let's just say that I was more than a little angry after waiting more time than I was told to have something that I could barely choke down. If I hadn't been working a double shift I would have just turned around and brought it back but as it was I had to get back to work I didn't have any more time and I wouldn't have any other food until tomorrow. Even with that I couldn't make myself finish it it just was not good. don't normally have to Salt my food and I certainly don't think to salt a pizza which I didn't in this case but it definitely felt like it needed a level of flavor up. it also took much longer than they said 5 to 10 minutes it was more like 15 to 20 and I was in a hurry.  I don't know if they changed the ingredients that they use in the pizza or they don't make the sauce anymore. Or if I just got some older dough combined with a flat sauce. Before today I would have said it's a great place to stop in and get Italian beef along with a tasty Little Italian Pizza. However currently my pizza endorsement stands as don't do it stick to an Italian  I started to call the restaurant to tell them how I felt but honestly there were four employees that I could see and the two who were in the front the two different young ladies I don't think they would have care not even a little bit. Which is unfortunate when they may not think of money as hard-earned but I certainly do
